The paper proposes a novel model-based policy search approach that leverages a weighting scheme to learn an approximate transition model. This approach falls under the category of reinforcement learning, which is typically associated with sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Given the focus on policy search and model-based learning, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.RO and cs.SY, which are relevant due to the potential applications in robotics and control. cs.NE is also a possible sub-category, given the use of neural networks in the proposed approach.
